      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "align": "center"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "url": "https://github.com/derrek-powell/reggaetonvoice/blob/main/images/S%20Indexical%20Field.png?raw=true",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "scale": 73,
      "align": "center",
      "caption": "Indexical Field of S-Reduction in Puerto Rico"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "align": "center"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "center",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Inspired by Delgado-Díaz et al (2021) and Mack (2011). Stances are marked with "
        },
        {
          "text": "italics",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "text": "traits/qualities",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " in bold, and speaker categories/voices in boxes. "
        },
        {
          "text": "Blue",
          "color": "#77a5ee"
        },
        {
          "text": " are indexical associations linked to sibilants /s/, black represents aspirations /h/, "
        },
        {
          "text": "green",
          "color": "#36ce40"
        },
        {
          "text": " glottal stops /ʔ/, and "
        },
        {
          "text": "red",
          "color": "#ce3636"
        },
        {
          "text": " full deletions. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
