    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This is a productive contrast that is identifiable across the music of different artists. It also remains present in collaborations where multiple voices associated with different genres and styles sing together. That is, even within the same composition, reduced /s/ variants delineate sonic, thematic, and poetic space through their association with distinct musical lineages. For example, in \"Bella y Sensual\", Daddy Yankee remains almost categorically s-less in contrast to the bachata singer Romeo Santos, who is near categorically s-full, despite both vocalists being of Hispano-Caribbean origins. "
        }
      ],
      "align": "justify"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "justify",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "includes": [
        "media",
