          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Below are some figures that trace patterns of s-reduction distributions between singers, genres, and over time to further showcase this convergence toward a standardized singing style. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "justify",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "justify",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grid",
      "layout": [
        2,
        4
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Powell (2025) examined /s/ production by artists of three unique Hispano-Caribbean origins (Cuba, Dominican Republic, and Puerto Rico respectively) across market-imposed genre categories. Each artist showed a preference for reduction in performances marketed as Latin Urban as opposed to music marketed as Tropical. While individual rates of reduction varied by artist, overall, the directions of effect were uniform, and the contrast between genres was quite stark. "
                }
              ],
              "align": "justify"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://github.com/derrek-powell/reggaetonvoice/blob/main/images/S%20by%20genre.png?raw=true",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ],
              "scale": 65,
              "align": "center"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "justify",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grid",
      "layout": [
        2,
        4
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Hayes (2023) found that both Bad Bunny and J Balvin use s-reduction at different rates between interviews and their music. Accordingly, J Balvin uses significantly more /s/ in his interviews that his music, whereas Bad Bunny favors more /s/ in his music than interviews. While the overall rate of reduction exhibits a stark contrast between artists when singing, Hayes finds that the direction of effect from interviews to music actually suggests a convergence toward a \"middle ground\". This is interpreted as alignment with an emergent phonological norm in reggaetón. "
                }
              ],
              "align": "justify"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ],
              "align": "center"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://github.com/derrek-powell/reggaetonvoice/blob/main/images/Hayes_Sreduction.png?raw=true",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grid",
      "layout": [
        2,
        4
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Powell (2024) found a similar convergence as Hayes in the performances of Anitta, Becky G, Karol G, and Natti Natasha. This study also identified that the prioritization of reduced variants has become more apparent in more recent years, in particular following the unprecedented success of Despacito. Moreover, this study found that the presence and demographics of collaborating artists could influence production, such that Becky G was more likely to reduce variants when performing with a Caribbean artist rather than a Mexican performer. This suggests that /s/ reduction is not only a way of aligning with artistic conventions, but of tailoring the form of a performance to the imagined demographics of the target audience. "
                }
              ],
              "align": "justify"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://github.com/derrek-powell/reggaetonvoice/blob/main/images/languages-09-00292-g005.png?raw=true",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ],
              "scale": 66,
              "align": "center"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
